WEBVTT

00:00.930 --> 00:01.991
He's saying just good morning.

00:02.392 --> 00:04.554
So glad that you're joining us and welcome to the fall.

00:05.355 --> 00:06.377
School is back.

00:06.477 --> 00:09.320
We're starting a new ministry year and I want to welcome you.

00:09.340 --> 00:10.882
Some of you have been here for decades.

00:11.102 --> 00:13.185
Some of you have been with us for years.

00:13.465 --> 00:14.987
Some of you joined us over the summer.

00:15.367 --> 00:18.531
Some of you for the last year, no matter who you are, where you're coming from, your background.

00:18.932 --> 00:22.997
So glad that you're choosing to be part of us as we're going this coming here.

00:23.818 --> 00:27.442
A lot of you who have been with us for more than a little while know that

00:27.618 --> 00:32.910
At the beginning of COVID, my wife and I, my family, we moved, like many, many, many other people did.

00:33.271 --> 00:38.462
We moved to a small little village, about 35 minutes from here, 40 minutes from the Ajax location, that is.

00:38.503 --> 00:41.810
And my wife and I bought this big old Victorian house.

00:41.858 --> 00:44.741
and we started this massive two and a half year renovation.

00:44.801 --> 01:03.181
And so we did all this work, and then we actually built a garage for the first time since 1876, and then three months I've shared the story, after of course we built the garage, our neighbor's 120 foot Douglas first snapped, and a windstorm came down, flattened our brand new garage, which by the way, all of our Christmas gifts were in.

01:03.681 --> 01:11.730
And so that was like devastating, and then we tore the whole thing down, hundreds of thousands of dollars of damage, and then we rebuilt it again,

01:11.778 --> 01:18.969
and lived through the COVID moment and did all this stuff that house was painted for the first time, like in 40 years, restoring rotting wood, all this stuff.

01:19.429 --> 01:23.656
And finally, we were coming sort of to the end of most of the renovations.

01:24.197 --> 01:28.503
And then someone walked up to our door, knocked and said, we love your house.

01:28.844 --> 01:29.304
We're like, thanks.

01:29.324 --> 01:31.167
They're like, no, no, no, we want your house.

01:31.207 --> 01:34.192
And I was like, but we just did all this work.

01:34.332 --> 01:35.473
Anyway, they gave us an offer.

01:35.534 --> 01:36.595
We could not refuse.

01:36.735 --> 01:37.977
And I'm not complaining.

01:38.097 --> 01:39.279
I'm very, very thankful.

01:39.359 --> 01:41.202
But when all of that happened,

01:41.410 --> 01:43.554
we felt sort of anxious and blessed.

01:44.255 --> 01:46.118
And then we were like, well, where in the world are we going to go?

01:46.158 --> 01:55.414
Because we only needed a rental probably for five or six months and getting a rental in the first place anywhere in the GTA or beyond is almost impossible.

01:55.734 --> 01:58.198
Getting a rental for five or six months doesn't really exist.

01:58.819 --> 02:01.764
There's five of us plus two dogs and a cat.

02:01.784 --> 02:03.267
And I was like, Lord, we need a place.

02:03.307 --> 02:05.170
Well, amazingly, the real estate agent

02:05.282 --> 02:11.311
who brought the people to our door said, well, actually know another real estate agent who actually hasn't been able to sell their house.

02:11.391 --> 02:12.273
It's two minutes from here.

02:12.633 --> 02:13.294
Would you like it?

02:13.334 --> 02:14.096
We're like, yes.

02:14.356 --> 02:19.564
So we rented for five months and then we were like, we have no clue where we're going.

02:19.724 --> 02:20.926
And there wasn't a ton of houses.

02:21.727 --> 02:23.370
And so we were like just trusting the Lord.

02:23.430 --> 02:26.375
Genuinely he had done this and we were really thankful.

02:26.555 --> 02:29.319
And so I remember I took this moment and I was praying.

02:29.339 --> 02:30.882
I said, Lord, where do you want us to go?

02:30.902 --> 02:33.746
House, life, city, all of it.

02:34.274 --> 02:36.657
And I'll never forget what happened next.

02:37.518 --> 02:42.324
The Holy Spirit very clearly said to me, John, you don't get to talk to me about the next house.

02:42.345 --> 02:42.885
Go to your wife.

02:43.025 --> 02:45.829
And I was like, okay, great.

02:45.929 --> 02:51.056
So I went to Joe and I said, hey, Joanna, I had this really odd encounter with the Lord today.

02:51.076 --> 02:53.860
I'm not allowed to talk about the next house I'm supposed to talk to you.

02:53.940 --> 02:55.221
I'm supposed to ask you what you want.

02:55.301 --> 02:58.866
And then I said, I reminded her and myself that

02:59.010 --> 03:01.614
you know, even having choice about anything is blessing.

03:01.654 --> 03:03.437
It's a very first world experience.

03:03.858 --> 03:05.500
So I said, babe, what do you want?

03:05.560 --> 03:06.261
And she laughed.

03:06.281 --> 03:07.523
And she said, I don't know, I don't know.

03:07.623 --> 03:10.909
Well, I've always sort of wanted a pool and I like hills.

03:11.069 --> 03:12.251
And so I'd like a pool and a hill.

03:12.571 --> 03:16.037
And she walked away and I was like, Lord, hear her prayer.

03:16.457 --> 03:17.178
And that was it.

03:17.960 --> 03:24.069
Anyway, we were in the rental and it was winter and there was nothing and no houses were coming up.

03:24.089 --> 03:27.154
And then it popped into my mind when we first went to this little village

03:27.810 --> 03:34.765
Like three plus years ago, just looking around, I remember across the river, because in the middle of my little town, there's this gorgeous river that runs through it.

03:35.406 --> 03:40.797
On the other side of the river, there was this house my wife always loved, because it had a wraparound porch and it had four rocking chairs.

03:41.318 --> 03:42.401
So I said, well, why not?

03:42.461 --> 03:46.850
So I went over across the river, walked up the door, and just knocked at the door.

03:47.511 --> 03:48.754
The woman came to the door,

03:48.962 --> 03:50.885
And I said, hi, my name's John.

03:50.965 --> 03:51.626
We live in this street.

03:51.706 --> 03:52.507
Oh, I know that house.

03:52.567 --> 03:53.469
It's sort of like that there.

03:53.869 --> 03:55.071
I said, this is really weird.

03:55.111 --> 03:59.918
Someone bought our house, and we're in a rental, and my wife liked your rocking chairs and your porch.

04:00.078 --> 04:02.482
So I know it's a little weird, but I'm knocking.

04:02.522 --> 04:04.885
Are you interested in selling your house?

04:04.905 --> 04:05.907
And I haven't even seen it.

04:06.047 --> 04:06.668
And she laughed.

04:06.728 --> 04:08.190
And she said, look at what I'm wearing.

04:08.210 --> 04:09.592
And I'm like, whoa, that's really weird.

04:09.612 --> 04:10.013
What do you mean?

04:10.053 --> 04:11.174
She's like, no, look at what I'm wearing.

04:11.194 --> 04:11.835
And I said, what do you mean?

04:12.476 --> 04:14.299
And she said, well, I'm wearing paint clothes.

04:14.339 --> 04:16.402
I said, why are you wearing panty clothes?

04:16.546 --> 04:17.708
painting the house to sell it.

04:17.728 --> 04:18.409
Do you want to come in?

04:18.449 --> 04:19.850
And I'm like, uh, sure.

04:20.551 --> 04:25.538
So we walked through this beautiful old house was from 1875 and it was in great shape.

04:25.618 --> 04:34.430
And then I walked to the back of the house and my jaw dropped because by the way, from the front of the house or the back of the house, you can't see this because of trees and everything else.

04:34.490 --> 04:36.994
See the house was on a hill.

04:37.575 --> 04:40.218
And at the bottom of the hill, there was a, anyone want to say it?

04:40.819 --> 04:41.099
Cool.

04:42.041 --> 04:43.122
And I was like, you got to be joking.

04:44.258 --> 04:48.562
And so within six weeks, we privately bought that house.

04:48.582 --> 04:49.423
And it was pretty amazing.

04:50.984 --> 04:56.930
In three years, we packed and unpacked and packed again and unpacked six times.

04:58.592 --> 05:13.586
If there is an image or a series of words that explain our experience, I would say tired, nervous, excited, exhausted, adjusting, thankful, and I would even say now finally getting settled.

05:15.042 --> 05:22.055
And I thought, you know what, that personal journey that we've been through, I think literally mirrors what our church has been through.

05:22.075 --> 05:37.362
In 2019, some of you will remember me saying this, I sat with our staff and there was a lot going on and some difficulty and I said, you know, the reason why we don't have our expectations right as staff is because we keep thinking that we're decorating the old house we used to be in.

05:37.890 --> 05:40.454
like we're putting wallpaper up and putting back splashes on.

05:40.755 --> 05:42.097
And I said, no, no, we're in the muck.

05:42.177 --> 05:43.739
We're actually building a new foundation.

05:43.799 --> 05:46.303
The house we were all used to is gone.

05:46.343 --> 05:47.525
We're building a new house.

05:47.886 --> 05:49.248
That is why this is so difficult.

05:49.288 --> 05:51.952
That was said before the pandemic happened.

05:53.655 --> 05:56.459
And now we're in this new house.

05:58.563 --> 06:00.786
And this new house is where we're at.

06:02.018 --> 06:05.523
I said this to our staff just a few weeks ago prepping for this ministry year.

06:05.543 --> 06:11.891
I said, you know, the time of COVID as we knew it is over, the time of moving into this new house that we now call Sanctus is done.

06:11.931 --> 06:15.136
The time of grieving of what was is now over.

06:15.716 --> 06:17.198
This is a new place, a new house.

06:17.279 --> 06:18.600
It's time we move forward again.

06:18.640 --> 06:22.726
Last year was about really not just rebuilding, but building.

06:23.367 --> 06:25.369
And this year is now about momentum.

06:26.591 --> 06:28.754
So what I want to do is I want to take us all on a journey.

06:29.282 --> 06:33.869
And some of you have heard this 20 times, some of you once, some of you never.

06:34.630 --> 06:41.581
But the reason why I do this every year is because we as one church in multiple locations have to have the same understanding.

06:42.403 --> 06:50.075
So I want to take us on this journey that makes us uniquely who we are as a local church and actually distinguishes us from churches down the street.

06:50.135 --> 06:52.178
We're not better than them, just a little different.

06:52.578 --> 07:03.387
We originally called Steeple Hill Community Bible Church in Pickering at White's Road, and then we outgrew that, and then we moved into Ajax High School, and we were there for about three years, and then we moved into the Ajax location.

07:03.427 --> 07:22.564
This was miraculous how we were given this building, and we built this, and we were called Crowther's Creek Community Church, and then no one wanted to say Crowther's Creek Community Church anymore, so people just started calling us C4, and then that got branded, but then C4 became troubled because as we're helping global partners, it sounds more like weaponry than it does other things,

07:22.544 --> 07:28.872
Anyways, we took some time to pray, and actually there's a cool story about how the Lord gave us the name Sanctus and just pre-COVID.

07:29.232 --> 07:33.057
We were named Sanctus, and then we are now Sanctus post-COVID.

07:34.258 --> 07:35.440
But how did all that happen?

07:36.561 --> 07:39.304
Well, in 2005, I had just become a senior pastor.

07:40.085 --> 07:50.418
It was September, I just turned 30 years old, the old senior pastor, that had grown the church from 50 to 1,000, which by the way, in Canadian, in that Canadian moment was pretty unbelievable.

07:50.850 --> 07:51.712
He was still in the front row.

07:51.732 --> 07:53.034
He didn't leave, I think, until November.

07:53.875 --> 07:56.901
We were one site, one service, one location.

07:57.802 --> 07:58.704
We had a mission statement.

07:58.724 --> 08:03.212
We existed to make fully devoted followers of Jesus, but we had no vision statement, no understanding.

08:03.252 --> 08:04.734
We had no clue of what was next.

08:05.816 --> 08:07.138
I gave my first vision talk.

08:07.158 --> 08:11.506
I shared some of this in May of last year, in the last ministry year.

08:12.258 --> 08:17.385
In that very overwhelming and intense moment, I asked our church a series of questions that had not been asked before.

08:17.445 --> 08:22.672
I asked us as a church family, why had God given us the amount of people we already had?

08:24.014 --> 08:25.236
What was our future going to look like?

08:26.057 --> 08:27.899
Was God calling us to be something?

08:27.999 --> 08:30.303
If so, did we even know what that something was?

08:31.504 --> 08:38.674
So in that moment, for the first time I started casting vision and I began to paint, part of the future were now all living.

08:39.042 --> 08:46.821
In that first sermon, a senior pastor, I introduced something that was not court or our understanding, which now today is fundamental to our church.

08:46.901 --> 08:49.909
It's common faithfulness and unique assignment.

08:50.791 --> 08:52.616
Forgive the repetition, but I have to do this.

08:52.716 --> 08:53.618
It's so important.

08:54.050 --> 08:58.156
Acts chapter two is the most famous and fundamental description of common faithfulness.

08:58.737 --> 09:13.579
Every single church on earth, no matter denomination, size, cultural expression, big, small, big, mega church, house church, liturgical bells and smells, free flowing choruses or hymns, they all have to have this.

09:15.001 --> 09:18.186
This is how the early church functioned.

09:18.206 --> 09:18.766
Acts 242.

09:18.826 --> 09:23.954
They devoted themselves to the apostles' teaching, fellowship, breaking of bread,

09:24.226 --> 09:43.634
prayer.

09:44.386 --> 09:46.670
And God added to the number daily those who are being saved.

09:46.690 --> 09:49.815
So you've got biblical teaching right out of the scriptures.

09:49.835 --> 09:50.856
You've got community.

09:50.876 --> 09:51.778
You've got communion.

09:52.098 --> 09:52.900
You've got prayer.

09:52.960 --> 09:54.282
You've got the presence of God.

09:54.322 --> 09:55.203
You've got giving.

09:55.223 --> 09:56.205
You've got loving the poor.

09:56.245 --> 09:58.088
You've got large worship gatherings.

09:58.108 --> 09:59.791
You've got small house gatherings.

09:59.811 --> 10:00.692
You've got baptism.

10:01.013 --> 10:01.974
You've got evangelism.

10:02.134 --> 10:03.156
Every church is called to do this.

10:03.256 --> 10:05.620
This is common faithfulness.

10:05.640 --> 10:09.426
The very last words of Jesus also make up the other half of the coin.

10:10.370 --> 10:13.054
What was Jesus's last words before he ascended to heaven?

10:13.094 --> 10:22.267
Matthew 28, therefore, go and make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father, the Son, and the Spirit, and teaching them to obey everything I've taught you.

10:22.647 --> 10:25.031
And I am surely always with you to the very end of the age.

10:25.992 --> 10:27.133
That is common faithfulness.

10:28.636 --> 10:35.946
And then this is what I say every year, but beyond common faithfulness, because almost all churches just settle for common faithfulness.

10:37.168 --> 10:38.930
Sometimes out of holy listening,

10:39.202 --> 10:40.284
God gives vision.

10:41.847 --> 10:46.156
We, of course, believe here at Sanctus that Jesus speaks to congregations and movements uniquely.

10:47.459 --> 10:53.952
In the book of Revelation, he spoke differently to the church and Sardis, differently to the church in Philadelphia or Smyrna or Ephesus.

10:53.992 --> 10:58.841
The Bible is full of leaders being given God-issued assignments.

10:58.862 --> 11:01.106
The mission is the same.

11:01.890 --> 11:04.274
But specific callings are given much of the time to leaders.

11:04.334 --> 11:05.976
Moses, I called you to do this.

11:06.197 --> 11:06.838
Paul, do that.

11:06.918 --> 11:07.679
Philip, go there.

11:08.020 --> 11:13.649
We're fasting and praying in the Spirit said, and those moments, and this is critical, if God speaks uniquely.

11:13.829 --> 11:15.211
God doesn't always speak 24-7.

11:15.511 --> 11:16.493
It's just not true.

11:16.793 --> 11:22.322
But if he does, that should become the inception point for a dynamic vision of a local church.

11:23.344 --> 11:24.786
This, of course, implies being open.

11:25.378 --> 11:29.842
actually believing in unique assignment as possibility, learning to listen through spiritual disciplines.

11:29.882 --> 11:37.770
This presumes empowering people with spiritual gifts and being able to test what is from God, what's human, what's agenda, what's demonic and what's what you ate last night.

11:38.851 --> 11:43.916
So, mission, Acts 2, Matthew 28, is common faithfulness.

11:44.076 --> 11:45.878
It never changes in any environment.

11:47.119 --> 11:51.263
Visions are God-given and they're given for a season, then they're going to be replaced.

11:51.423 --> 11:52.124
It's like bread.

11:53.165 --> 11:54.386
Bread has a shelf life.

11:55.170 --> 11:56.993
and then it goes bad, or it's done.

11:57.013 --> 12:01.180
Now strategies support mission and vision, they can change at any time.

12:01.480 --> 12:02.863
Now does this mean God will always speak?

12:02.943 --> 12:03.824
No, he's not a genie.

12:04.205 --> 12:08.552
Much of the time common faithfulness is the only ongoing call from heaven.

12:08.953 --> 12:14.001
But to keep in step with Holy Spirit, you need to keep asking the Holy Spirit if there's a unique call.

12:14.021 --> 12:21.714
So that very first sermon, here's what I actually shared to our church and moved us for the first time from mission

12:21.794 --> 12:23.416
to vision by addressing two things.

12:23.456 --> 12:25.257
I talked about geography and size.

12:25.377 --> 12:27.239
Again, some of you will remember this from last May.

12:28.761 --> 12:31.223
It is here that the word regional was used for the first time.

12:31.884 --> 12:34.026
Our name back then was Crowther's Creek Community Church.

12:34.106 --> 12:42.413
So when people in 2005 heard Crowther's Creek Community Church, they literally thought we were going to reach the community physically behind the Ajax location.

12:42.554 --> 12:43.875
By the way, that was my old neighborhood.

12:44.856 --> 12:48.399
But I used to laugh about that because I was basically me and three others where the only ones that lived there.

12:49.660 --> 12:51.442
I said regional does not mean

12:51.522 --> 12:53.685
Our community does not mean my community.

12:54.225 --> 12:55.907
Then I started listing all these names of people.

12:55.928 --> 13:01.595
We have people in Scarborough and Pickering and Ajax and Whitby and Oshawa and Salina and Port Perry and Exbridge and Brooklyn and Rome.

13:01.675 --> 13:04.138
I said, God has strategically planted us.

13:04.178 --> 13:05.600
So we're actually regional.

13:05.620 --> 13:06.361
Let's just admit it.

13:07.822 --> 13:08.724
And then I shared this.

13:09.945 --> 13:14.090
I said, God is going to make us a church of thousands in this next chapter.

13:14.591 --> 13:17.074
And then I said, you know, churches have callings like people.

13:17.698 --> 13:19.582
We've been given certain gifts, leaders, and dreams.

13:20.223 --> 13:21.645
I said, but visions are different.

13:22.086 --> 13:23.228
Some are called to be small.

13:24.070 --> 13:25.292
Some are called to church plant.

13:25.873 --> 13:31.624
Some are called to build house church networks, but we're called to be a gathered church of thousands.

13:32.486 --> 13:34.770
That was the first inkling at vision.

13:35.554 --> 13:36.696
Well, all sorts of people.

13:36.896 --> 13:38.479
I remember that month were excited.

13:38.859 --> 13:43.527
Many, many more thought I was young and petuous, ambitious, full of pride.

13:43.547 --> 13:47.192
I was trying to build a big church because I wanted to be like a mega church pastor.

13:47.833 --> 13:50.137
And this was all about me and my kingdom and many left.

13:51.419 --> 13:52.441
Well, fast forward, we grew.

13:52.481 --> 13:55.646
And five years later, we became even more bold.

13:56.447 --> 13:59.372
It was 2010 and our mission statement had changed a little bit.

13:59.532 --> 14:01.054
It read like this, to glorify God.

14:01.195 --> 14:03.378
Oh, we made sure that God was no central.

14:04.162 --> 14:07.791
by enabling people of all ages to become fully devoted followers of Jesus Christ.

14:08.472 --> 14:08.713
Great.

14:09.635 --> 14:13.825
But in 2010, in that series, I also slowed down and said, hold on, hold on.

14:14.346 --> 14:17.794
We want to enable people to become fully devoted followers of Jesus.

14:17.834 --> 14:20.360
But here's the question, who are the people?

14:22.365 --> 14:22.706
Well,

14:23.010 --> 14:28.197
I said, there are tons of people, of course, that have joined our church and are part of our church that are followers of Jesus.

14:28.257 --> 14:31.120
They've said, yes, to Jesus, a Savior, leader, and Lord.

14:31.160 --> 14:37.969
And so we need to grow and encourage them, of course, to walk with God, grow in our faith, contribute to the faith community and impact the world for Christ.

14:38.069 --> 14:38.370
Yes.

14:38.790 --> 14:41.834
But then I said, but who are the people we're trying to reach who don't know Jesus yet?

14:43.236 --> 14:44.638
And this is what I said in 2010.

14:45.158 --> 14:49.624
We want our church to see different groups of people come all at once.

14:49.644 --> 14:51.026
We want irreligious people.

14:51.170 --> 14:59.019
those people that have no faith, agnostic, atheist, humanists, those who only live in the now to become fully devoted followers of Jesus.

14:59.920 --> 15:06.067
We want those who are spiritual and new age and vibey to encounter the true living God.

15:06.988 --> 15:15.698
We want others who are part of formal other religions to meet Jesus, the only Savior, the only true God, the only answer to this life and the life to come.

15:16.642 --> 15:17.483
And then I said this too.

15:17.543 --> 15:21.370
We're also called to reach a very large group around us called nominal Christians.

15:22.271 --> 15:26.197
These are the hundreds of thousands of people that are Christians in name only.

15:26.538 --> 15:28.701
Some are religious, some aren't that religious.

15:29.062 --> 15:30.584
Some are Holly and Lily Christians.

15:30.604 --> 15:31.926
They come at Christmas and Easter.

15:32.327 --> 15:34.691
Some are practicing, some are non-practicing.

15:34.751 --> 15:38.256
Many give intellectual assent sort of to basic Christian thought.

15:38.296 --> 15:39.979
They might attend a worship service.

15:40.240 --> 15:42.944
They might be a really active member in their local church.

15:43.064 --> 15:44.306
But in spite of all this,

15:44.610 --> 15:49.759
I said they're destined for eternal judgment because they've not actually committed their life personally to Jesus Christ.

15:50.701 --> 15:54.448
I think it's probably about being good or being moral, but not about faith in Jesus.

15:55.289 --> 15:57.754
And I said our purpose is to see all these people come to faith.

15:59.657 --> 16:06.610
So that was like a defining moment, but in that 2010 series, though we had grown over the five years,

16:07.266 --> 16:12.777
And though our vision said we'd reached thousands, it was still blurry and unclear and caused disunity in our church.

16:12.797 --> 16:20.112
So in 2010, in that same sermon, we finally publicly spoke about what we had prayed over, talked about, and agreed upon before.

16:20.853 --> 16:27.346
In that very sermon, I had then started saying, if our mission is that and the people are these people,

16:27.906 --> 16:29.748
then what's our actual vision statement?

16:29.768 --> 16:37.239
And I started saying this, you know, one person brilliantly said, a vision is a clear mental picture of a preferable future given by God.

16:37.319 --> 16:37.839
That's vision.

16:39.301 --> 16:42.586
And then these are the words I shared all those years ago now.

16:44.028 --> 16:46.431
John reads an old church.

16:47.132 --> 16:49.375
Thousands fully devoted, doing kingdom things.

16:50.076 --> 16:50.977
But where's the glue?

16:51.938 --> 16:55.022
Can you fit our vision on a t-shirt?

16:55.223 --> 16:57.746
And I said, yes.

16:57.826 --> 16:58.868
Here's where we're really going.

17:00.009 --> 17:05.498
To become a regional church of 10,000, meaning the physical, emotional, and spiritual needs of people in Jesus' name.

17:06.660 --> 17:12.448
Well, when I said that like I shared in May, the oxygen, unless there were a few people clapped, some people gasped, everyone's like, what?

17:13.330 --> 17:14.311
I said, let me walk this through.

17:15.132 --> 17:16.214
Again, regional church.

17:17.156 --> 17:19.479
We travel 30 seconds to 25 minutes.

17:20.581 --> 17:21.362
So we're regional.

17:21.858 --> 17:27.164
Not only that, by that point in 2010, we were now involved in national things and we were involved in global endeavors.

17:27.564 --> 17:28.685
And so we were like, you know what?

17:29.646 --> 17:30.567
This is getting pretty big.

17:31.528 --> 17:33.010
And then I said, a church of 10,000.

17:33.030 --> 17:36.734
And I pretended someone was asking me, John, where did that come from?

17:37.575 --> 17:40.939
I mean, was this a number just out of the air that seemed like a big enough challenge?

17:41.359 --> 17:44.903
Did you go to Texas and go, oh my goodness, we need to become some American mega church?

17:45.424 --> 17:48.106
I said, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

17:48.327 --> 17:49.067
Here's the background.

17:50.389 --> 17:51.410
In 2004,

17:52.258 --> 17:53.800
I went to an event called Missions Fest.

17:54.942 --> 18:00.710
I didn't want to go to Missions Fest because I'm the child of missionaries and didn't like Missions Fest and didn't want to hang out with that crowd.

18:01.932 --> 18:05.437
During a devotional time, I was instructed by the Holy Spirit, you need to go.

18:05.457 --> 18:08.881
And not just go, I was told to go to listen to one person.

18:09.502 --> 18:14.930
And I said to the Holy Spirit, I don't want to go listen to that one person because that one person is actually like

18:15.010 --> 18:17.794
not just Pentecostal, he's ultra Pentecostal and all sorts of things.

18:17.854 --> 18:19.697
And I don't agree with so much of what he said.

18:19.717 --> 18:20.798
And the Holy Spirit said, go.

18:20.898 --> 18:21.900
And I was like, shoot.

18:22.060 --> 18:22.481
So I did.

18:23.582 --> 18:26.106
So I went and I sat and listened.

18:26.186 --> 18:32.014
And suddenly, while that guy was preaching, the Holy Spirit said, John, pray for 10,000 at C4.

18:32.054 --> 18:34.898
And I said to God, there is no way I'm, no.

18:35.426 --> 18:36.467
I am a Canadian.

18:36.528 --> 18:38.070
This is not the US.

18:38.691 --> 18:41.054
This is not in parts of Asia or Africa.

18:41.074 --> 18:41.835
I will not do it."

18:41.875 --> 18:43.137
And God said, you must do it.

18:43.177 --> 18:44.198
I said, I will not do it.

18:44.539 --> 18:45.200
I wrestled with him.

18:45.220 --> 18:49.606
I finally got on my lease and said, if this is you speaking, Lord, 10,000 to C4.

18:49.626 --> 18:50.327
I don't get it.

18:51.208 --> 18:53.692
Months later, I was doing my devotions, reading through Genesis.

18:53.732 --> 18:55.154
It was a boring, normal day.

18:55.426 --> 18:59.712
And that day I was reading in Genesis 41, reading through the Bible, where Joseph is brought before Pharaoh.

18:59.732 --> 19:00.553
He's made Prime Minister.

19:01.295 --> 19:06.242
And as I was reading the passage, again, this very unique moment, the Holy Spirit said, I'm going to give you more.

19:07.063 --> 19:08.144
I said, more, I love what I'm doing.

19:08.285 --> 19:09.667
The youth group was exploding.

19:09.687 --> 19:10.868
The young adults was exploding.

19:11.229 --> 19:11.850
Preteens.

19:11.890 --> 19:12.891
And he said, no, no, no.

19:12.911 --> 19:13.833
Read verse 46.

19:15.054 --> 19:18.319
Joseph was 30 years old when he entered the service of Pharaoh King of Egypt.

19:18.339 --> 19:21.664
And I heard, John, you're going to be the senior pastor of this church by 30.

19:21.684 --> 19:23.026
And I was like, what?

19:23.106 --> 19:23.667
No, I'm not.

19:23.727 --> 19:25.369
And that's inappropriate and that's wrong.

19:25.409 --> 19:26.911
And that's my pride speaking.

19:26.951 --> 19:27.932
And no, no, no.

19:27.972 --> 19:29.874
And Dave hasn't told me that he's leaving.

19:29.914 --> 19:30.875
That's Dave Collins.

19:30.975 --> 19:39.846
And well, after amounts of questioning and wrestling and feeling quite guilty, Dave suddenly told us that he was leaving our church and God had told them to.

19:39.866 --> 19:43.170
And then he looked at me and a staff meeting and said, you're supposed to take over.

19:43.871 --> 19:46.875
And then the elders met and they said, yeah, actually you are supposed to take over.

19:47.836 --> 19:49.778
And only then and at that moment.

19:51.042 --> 19:55.690
I met with the elders and the pastors and I told them about the Genesis 41 moment.

19:55.710 --> 20:01.040
And also during that period, I actually sat them down and I told them what I was praying over our church, the number.

20:01.981 --> 20:10.616
So every elders board from 2005 to 2010 and the pastoral staff had prayed and tested what I had heard.

20:11.498 --> 20:13.842
I submitted and there was agreement it was from the Lord.

20:16.002 --> 20:18.146
Then I asked this question, OK, John, why didn't you tell us sooner?

20:18.206 --> 20:20.150
And I said, well, honestly, a mix of things, fear.

20:20.270 --> 20:20.951
What would you think?

20:21.071 --> 20:23.556
What I deal with it?

20:23.877 --> 20:24.718
Would we rally?

20:24.838 --> 20:25.560
Were we ready?

20:25.580 --> 20:28.405
Did God need to get us to a place to think bigger than we had been?

20:28.485 --> 20:32.673
There are 1,000 reasons from taking time to discern, to deep wondering.

20:32.773 --> 20:39.666
But then I said, in 2010, I stand here today declaring that the board and the staff have fastened and prayed, and we believe this is our assignment.

20:40.642 --> 20:48.314
And then I said, you know, there's a lot of fear when it comes to 10,000 because few of us have experienced Christian community in that size to be a church of 10,000 is sizable.

20:48.714 --> 20:50.657
And then I said, so do I think bigger is better?

20:50.677 --> 20:53.061
Are all churches called to be large churches?

20:53.401 --> 20:55.945
Are small churches less important to God or failing?

20:55.965 --> 21:01.053
I said, no, this has to do with vision and assignment.

21:02.575 --> 21:04.338
The following Sunday I got up and said,

21:05.090 --> 21:10.797
You know, in God's sovereignty, if He made us 10,000 people tomorrow, a real awakening took place.

21:10.817 --> 21:12.119
And 10,000 people are with us.

21:12.520 --> 21:21.111
I said to the church, you realize that we would have reached 0.16% of the GTA, not even a half a percent of the GTA would have been reached.

21:21.691 --> 21:23.434
I said it's huge, but it's not, right?

21:24.836 --> 21:26.738
Well, after that moment, we launched Plan 1.

21:26.914 --> 21:28.015
that helped us move forward.

21:28.035 --> 21:29.837
They were to our God-given vision.

21:29.897 --> 21:32.078
This was direct, followable steps.

21:32.519 --> 21:34.561
This is when multi-site was introduced.

21:34.601 --> 21:37.263
This is when alpha was introduced formally in a bigger way.

21:37.583 --> 21:40.125
This is when releasing prayer was introduced more formally.

21:40.466 --> 21:46.391
We moved from one service and one site to many services at one site to many services at more sites.

21:46.491 --> 21:50.134
And then we started finding what is a fully devoted follower look like.

21:50.174 --> 21:54.058
And then we started introducing things like guaranteed places of encounter.

21:54.538 --> 21:56.900
And then we started talking about spiritual gifts,

21:56.880 --> 22:01.146
for the first time in spiritual disciplines and how they're key to renewal.

22:01.246 --> 22:08.156
And then we experienced a three-year documented renewal that was life-changing for hundreds of us, thousands of us.

22:09.458 --> 22:12.562
So let me summarize it like this, in 2005, the next chapter started.

22:12.582 --> 22:24.178
2010, mission and vision are clarified, then plan one is introduced, then common language run fully devoted followers, then gifts, then disciplines, and then, and then, and then, and then we came to 2015.

22:25.186 --> 22:26.087
Our mission's clear.

22:26.208 --> 22:27.169
Our vision is clear.

22:27.209 --> 22:28.952
Our plans are actually being followed.

22:28.972 --> 22:29.853
We're moving forward.

22:30.454 --> 22:34.801
And then I said, you know, there's one other missing piece to the puzzle we need to talk about.

22:35.442 --> 22:42.212
We need to talk about what our flavor, our picture, what our cultural vision is going to look like.

22:42.232 --> 22:43.514
It's an interesting story.

22:44.616 --> 22:47.000
This summer we had friends of ours come over for dinner.

22:47.040 --> 22:48.883
They live in England.

22:48.903 --> 22:49.904
Let me tell you their story.

22:49.984 --> 22:53.650
They both were teenagers in the youth group when I was the youth pastor here.

22:54.242 --> 22:56.305
And maybe some of you have heard the story.

22:56.325 --> 23:00.290
So I was preaching in the Ajax auditorium as the youth pastor on a Sunday night.

23:00.390 --> 23:02.553
And I remember this guy raising his hands.

23:03.213 --> 23:09.021
And I remember watching him and going, oh, someone from a charismatic or Pentecostal church is visiting.

23:09.041 --> 23:12.946
Because back then, me and like three other people rose our hands and most other people didn't.

23:13.266 --> 23:15.549
So I was like, oh, we got a Pentecostal hangout.

23:15.589 --> 23:17.151
I'm like, great.

23:17.692 --> 23:20.155
So I walked over to Esther who had brought him.

23:20.195 --> 23:21.817
And I said, Esther, who's your Pentecostal friend?

23:21.857 --> 23:22.418
And she laughed.

23:23.266 --> 23:24.748
She's like, what do you mean, Pentecostal friend?

23:25.289 --> 23:30.217
He's a Marxist atheist who just radically encountered Jesus while you were preaching.

23:30.237 --> 23:30.959
I said, excuse me?

23:32.161 --> 23:34.244
She's like, yeah, he's like basically a hardcore.

23:34.625 --> 23:36.107
He had Anglican history and met with him.

23:36.147 --> 23:40.154
I talked with him and he just, all these connections, this, God did this incredible thing.

23:40.334 --> 23:42.998
A few weeks later, he's hanging out at youth group again.

23:43.038 --> 23:46.324
He walks up and says, hey, John, what's the word missionary?

23:46.424 --> 23:48.628
It's ringing in my head and I don't understand it.

23:48.648 --> 23:50.130
And I explained what it was.

23:50.274 --> 23:55.601
And then we actually, over that year, prayed that Lord you'd use him as a missionary, whatever that would mean.

23:56.703 --> 23:59.567
Well, fast forward, those two people married.

24:00.969 --> 24:03.051
And they started quite an academic career.

24:03.192 --> 24:07.658
One of them got a PhD, one of the top universities in the United States, the thing in biochemistry.

24:07.678 --> 24:10.802
He ends up doing his PhD in one of the top

24:11.106 --> 24:15.713
universities in England in medieval philosophy, if you could imagine.

24:16.274 --> 24:23.746
And now he's a professor at Cambridge University in philosophy and she oversees a massive, she's a key editor in her journal.

24:23.766 --> 24:24.627
Here's the point.

24:25.348 --> 24:29.415
There, now back at our church, hanging out all these years later, we have them over for dinner.

24:29.775 --> 24:31.237
And he says, you know, it's so incredible.

24:31.358 --> 24:34.983
I'm the only Christian in the whole philosophy department where I work.

24:35.564 --> 24:39.250
And she smiled and said, yeah, we're missionaries at Cambridge.

24:40.258 --> 24:41.480
And then she said these words.

24:41.540 --> 24:43.043
She said, you know, John, it's so interesting.

24:43.964 --> 24:57.446
She said, we were reflecting on our own story, but then we have so many friends that were from Steeple Hill and Credis Creek in C4 and Sanctus that have become pastors themselves or aren't pastors, but are just all around the world.

24:57.486 --> 25:00.491
And she said, like, how do I describe this church?

25:00.531 --> 25:07.282
She said, it feels like a mother church to me, like a church that just sends out so many people as it grows itself, she said,

25:07.362 --> 25:09.144
It's, this is literally like three weeks ago.

25:09.184 --> 25:12.549
She says, it's just like you guys are like, what church was that in the book of Acts?

25:12.629 --> 25:14.071
Oh, Antioch, and I laughed.

25:15.553 --> 25:16.394
And she's like, why are you laughing?

25:16.434 --> 25:22.142
I said, because you don't know this, but in 2015, we've been saying that we need to be like Antioch.

25:22.162 --> 25:26.067
That's our cultural goal and ongoing desire to be.

25:26.307 --> 25:31.314
Let me read, by the way, Acts 12, 26, the disciples were first called Christians and Antioch, and

25:31.458 --> 25:40.815
Acts 13.1, in the church at Antioch, there were prophets and teachers, Barnabas, Simon of Niger, Lucius of Cyrene, Manian, who had been brought up with Herod the Tetrarch and Saul.

25:40.855 --> 25:46.245
And every time I've preached this, I say, stop and see the revolutionary power of the gospel.

25:46.826 --> 25:53.298
You've got Jews and Greeks and Romans meeting in a church together for a year, and the list is wild.

25:53.346 --> 26:07.738
Saul, who used to kill Christians, hanging it with Barnabas, who's one of the early Christian leaders, and then Simon of Niger, who, that's a Latin title because he had darker skin, so he was probably in the middle or from the south of Africa somewhere in his origin.

26:07.799 --> 26:23.332
Lucius is a common Roman name, but Cyrene is North African, it's modern day Libya, and then Mannion is the foster brother of Herod, who the wise men talk to, who ends up getting drunk and beheading John the Baptist, and now he's a church leader, and he's following

26:23.312 --> 26:46.039
Christ and so I said what's incredible you've got Jews and non-Jews and Africans and North Africans and Romans and Greeks and the list goes on and God through the work of Jesus through his spirit brings people together that cannot stand each other that are former enemies that would never hang out religious ethically economically or socially and now they're all worshiping Jesus and leading a church together.

26:47.020 --> 26:51.826
And I said of course this is what we need to be not just because we live in the most multicultural city on earth

26:52.354 --> 26:54.937
which is amazing, but this is what heaven's going to be like.

26:55.478 --> 26:56.780
So we fight for this now.

26:57.020 --> 26:58.983
We don't just wait for it in the future.

26:59.904 --> 27:07.575
And then it says in Acts 13, too, whether you're worshiping the Lord in fasting, the spirit of God spoke, set apart, Bartubus and Saul for the work to which I have called them.

27:07.595 --> 27:11.560
Now that word worshiping, I shared this again with our staff a few weeks ago, has real punch.

27:11.900 --> 27:19.090
The word worship here in the Greek version of the Old Testament is used almost exclusively for priests in the Jewish temple.

27:19.266 --> 27:30.617
And what's so shocking about this is this is now saying that Jewish and non-Jewish Christians, when they get together in church to fast, to pray, to be taught, and use spiritual gifts, it equals work in the new temple.

27:31.778 --> 27:36.863
And in the middle of this amazing moment, the Spirit of God through this spiritual gift of prophecy speaks.

27:37.484 --> 27:42.609
And he tells that community the will of Jesus who runs and owns the Church of Antioch.

27:43.029 --> 27:45.712
And this is what happens during basically a renewal.

27:45.792 --> 27:48.114
He said, I want to remove

27:48.610 --> 27:50.933
You're two most eminent and gifted leaders.

27:51.614 --> 27:54.457
You're two best thinkers, you're two best preachers, you're two most anointed.

27:54.958 --> 28:04.289
Actually, I was saying this the other day to someone, Paul, who is like the best version of a leader and Barnabas, who's the best version of a shepherd and encourager.

28:04.429 --> 28:11.097
So I'm basically gonna remove both sides of the best styles of leadership at once.

28:12.238 --> 28:13.260
When does the prompting happen?

28:13.981 --> 28:16.183
During the time of praying and fasting.

28:16.544 --> 28:18.546
So I just wanna say this again.

28:19.426 --> 28:22.952
This is so core to what we believe in this church.

28:24.033 --> 28:29.422
Spiritual gifts are the only ongoing guaranteed place of power to serve from all the time.

28:30.123 --> 28:41.441
And spiritual practices become the ongoing place where we are transformed, we are changed, they clear the ground, they provide the space so we get to hear and get permission and keep in step of the Spirit.

28:41.922 --> 28:44.626
Jesus was led exclusively by the Spirit.

28:45.058 --> 28:48.143
and use spiritual gifts to minister and spiritual disciplines to listen.

28:48.503 --> 28:53.330
So local churches should have the same posture as Jesus himself.

28:54.231 --> 29:06.049
And by the way, if you're new to us as a church, if you're new in this church, but you come from another church, what I just said is probably very different than what you're used to hearing.

29:06.810 --> 29:09.714
And so I just want to pause and say to really understand what you're joining.

29:10.242 --> 29:11.543
You need to think through this one well.

29:11.563 --> 29:18.890
You can go listen to the spiritual disciplines or guest sermons we did or the book convergence that tells our story, which is available.

29:18.910 --> 29:23.475
You can just ask any staff member that will tell you where we theologically land here and why.

29:24.256 --> 29:31.903
This is what makes us not better, but a different, we're a different breed compared to many other churches regionally.

29:31.923 --> 29:39.250
So Antioch, I said in 2015, that's our archetype, our flavor, our cultural vision, a place of strong biblical teaching.

29:39.586 --> 29:42.529
A place of influence for the kingdom and its own region and beyond.

29:43.169 --> 29:58.985
Spiritual disciplines, mutual submission, strong leadership, growing in cultural diversity, all the spiritual gifts at the center of serving, sensitivity to the spirit's leading, prompting, planning, the staying and going of leaders as the spirit of God moves.

29:59.505 --> 30:01.547
This is the type of church God is calling us to be.

30:01.907 --> 30:08.754
This is our God-given flavor, rooted in God the Father's calling, rooted in the work of Jesus, rooted in the power of the Holy Spirit.

30:10.018 --> 30:13.702
Well, that was in 2015 and lots has happened in eight years.

30:14.582 --> 30:18.106
Plan one ended, plan two was thought, prayed through, and built.

30:19.007 --> 30:23.731
We launched it and then eight months into plan two, the pandemic started.

30:23.771 --> 30:27.175
And we walked through a pandemic together, barely.

30:28.115 --> 30:33.160
We've moved from one site in 2005 and one service now to five sites and eight services.

30:34.261 --> 30:39.026
Thousands upon thousands of people have joined this church since 2005.

30:39.618 --> 30:40.680
Many of us have stayed.

30:41.461 --> 30:44.806
Many of us have moved out of the province to other countries or regions.

30:45.387 --> 30:46.749
Others have joined other churches.

30:46.890 --> 30:48.552
Others have actually started other churches.

30:48.993 --> 30:50.616
Some have been called into ministry.

30:50.796 --> 30:51.858
Some have passed away.

30:52.739 --> 30:54.001
But so much work has been done.

30:55.664 --> 31:03.276
A renewal that lasted three years, a name change, our multicultural experience, which was a long for desire, is now exploding.

31:05.179 --> 31:06.962
Last May, in April,

31:07.746 --> 31:16.259
The elders and staff sat and asked a question as we were preparing to move from a transitional moment of COVID and building now to momentum.

31:17.281 --> 31:18.342
We just said, hold on, hold on.

31:18.382 --> 31:26.415
Before we prepare for this next chapter, is there anything in our coreness, our mission or vision that we need to adjust?

31:26.475 --> 31:30.040
Has anything moved from aspirational now to DNA?

31:31.022 --> 31:36.370
And so we announced in May that there were two significant adjustments in our mission and vision statement.

31:37.058 --> 31:46.867
Our mission statement, sorry reads like this now, to glorify God by reaching enabling people of all ages and nations to become fully devoted followers of Jesus.

31:48.028 --> 32:01.321
We wanted to continue to realize that at different ages and stages, different evangelism and different discipleship is needed, but we also wanted to honor, fight for, pray into, and celebrate God's diversity.

32:02.942 --> 32:07.026
And then we unveiled the next iteration of the mission statement.

32:08.226 --> 32:10.250
We changed the word regional and made it missional.

32:10.270 --> 32:17.345
It reads like this now, a missional church of 10,000, meaning a spiritual, emotional, and physical needs of people in Jesus' name.

32:17.405 --> 32:19.309
We changed regional to missional.

32:19.349 --> 32:20.612
Again, let me just do this quickly.

32:20.973 --> 32:24.781
When I first talked about regionality, it meant behind the Ajax location.

32:25.663 --> 32:27.186
Then it meant Durham region.

32:27.842 --> 32:30.446
And just before the pandemic, we revealed plan two.

32:30.686 --> 32:40.260
And in that plan, remember, we talked about multiple new sites, Oakville, Markham, Stoweville, downtown Toronto, North York, Lindsay or Peterborough, or in Port Hope.

32:40.281 --> 32:43.706
All of that came to a standstill as we lived through that terrible global moment.

32:44.447 --> 32:48.773
And our goal, God willing, is still in time to launch many new sites across the GTA.

32:49.154 --> 32:57.426
But what's interesting is during the pandemic, our global reach, our global reach, which we knew was happening, got formalized.

32:57.922 --> 33:11.641
our influence because of our online presence exploded way beyond the GTA, all over the world through sermons and on our online site and books and worship writing and gatherings, everything changed.

33:12.663 --> 33:14.966
And so the word missional is global.

33:15.787 --> 33:17.089
The word missional is local.

33:17.630 --> 33:20.654
It gives room for virtual and physical and mixed expressions of church.

33:21.035 --> 33:26.322
It also reminds us we need to keep pushing out and not be satisfied with where we are now.

33:27.010 --> 33:44.326
It's also interesting, let me just note this too, that as we've gone through all sorts of iterations, it would seem to me at least, and I think actually to our leadership, that though we're a very large church, a church of thousands, as we keep spreading out, many of our expressions feel like smaller churches.

33:45.147 --> 33:56.658
So it's this really interesting new thing that's happening that we're a very large church, a church of thousands, and yet we have larger and smaller expressions happening in one ecosystem.

33:57.218 --> 34:03.224
which I think is probably God's design as we reach out to a new generation.

34:04.785 --> 34:07.088
And so, let me put it like this.

34:08.369 --> 34:18.139
We're in our new house, and we've been building the new house, re-establishing a few things, but actually building a lot of new things, and now it's time to step out again.

34:19.500 --> 34:25.586
And so, we shouldn't be shocked by the theme that was given to us last November,

34:25.762 --> 34:33.349
We spent time praying about this year, and we all say, Lord, is there something not just for the whole church long term?

34:33.530 --> 34:34.871
Is there something you want to speak this year?

34:35.171 --> 34:45.962
And it was so interesting, back in November, as we were praying about this coming year, it was very clear that the phrase that was given to our church is origins or beginnings.

34:47.223 --> 34:50.466
And I was like, oh, of course, because this is a new beginning.

34:51.107 --> 34:54.130
But as we have a new beginning, we also need to remember our origin.

34:54.658 --> 34:57.702
And then clear as day as we were praying through, what should we preach?

34:57.722 --> 35:03.749
The critical book that was given to us, we would say by the spirit for our community was the Book of Acts.

35:03.769 --> 35:05.551
And I'm like, well, of course it's the Book of Acts.

35:06.052 --> 35:07.594
Of course we're gonna go through the Book of Acts.

35:07.634 --> 35:10.677
Of course it's not Nehemiah about rebuilding or Ezekiel.

35:10.697 --> 35:11.438
No, no, or Ezra.

35:11.458 --> 35:24.434
No, no, beginnings, momentum, empowerment of the Holy Spirit, miracles, gifts, multiculturalism, evangelism, leadership transitions, church tension, discipleship, of course.

35:24.834 --> 35:27.057
the Holy Spirit's asking us to go through the Book of Acts.

35:27.918 --> 35:30.602
I said this to our staff a few weeks ago and our elders, I want to say it to you.

35:30.622 --> 35:34.407
That should build real expectation.

35:35.388 --> 35:37.331
You know that I'm cautious about expectation.

35:37.351 --> 35:41.557
I never like under-promising, but I never love over-promising either.

35:42.538 --> 35:54.194
But this should build expectation because if the Spirit of God has prompted us to go through the Book of Acts, then the expectation should grow among us because that means he is actually about to begin a new thing.

35:54.946 --> 36:02.837
And the book of Acts is all about empowerment, and the book of Acts is all about evangelism, and the book of Acts is all about new life, even while there are battles.

36:04.018 --> 36:08.484
And so there should be a real expectation that God is about to move actually quite profoundly.

36:09.526 --> 36:21.982
And so what I'm gonna do to end this sort of vision moment is would you stand, again, if you are at any location, or maybe by yourself, or maybe you're in a gathering in a house, but would you do it?

36:22.283 --> 36:23.364
And let's just pray this together.

36:23.384 --> 36:24.626
Lord, thanks for our history.

36:25.570 --> 36:30.715
Thanks that you've been with us for every single iteration and chapter and moment.

36:32.076 --> 36:33.037
Thanks for the old house.

36:33.698 --> 36:36.100
Thanks for persevering during the global moment.

36:36.781 --> 36:37.902
Thanks for this new house.

36:38.923 --> 36:41.445
And now a father and son send the Holy Spirit.

36:42.146 --> 36:48.392
May we as a church not just read the book of Acts and intellectually learn the truth in the book of Acts.

36:48.932 --> 36:53.456
May we at Sanctus Church experience the book of Acts.

36:54.377 --> 36:55.218
In Bowmanville,

36:55.778 --> 36:59.325
for parry, pickering, Ajax, online, and beyond.

37:00.347 --> 37:05.498
Father and Son, we as a church say, send the Holy Spirit and move us out again, we ask.

37:05.578 --> 37:06.981
In Jesus' name, we all sit together.

37:09.085 --> 37:09.426
Amen.

